<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="150" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,521]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,221,244]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Biswas" box="[316,550,221,244]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" refString="Biswas, B. &amp; Roy, R. (2008) Description of six new species of spiders of the genera Lathys (Family: Dictynidae), Marpissa (Family: Salticidae), Misumenoides (Family: Thomisidae), Agroeca (Family: Clubionidae), Gnaphosa (Family: Gnaphosidae) and Flanona (Family: Lycosidae) from India. Records of the Zoological Survey of India, 108, 43 - 57." type="journal article" year="2008">Biswas &amp; Roy (2008)</bibRefCitation>
described this species based on a single female specimen from Garwall (Garhwal) Hills in the northern Indian state of 
<collectingRegion box="[566,697,256,279]" country="India" name="Uttarakhand" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">Uttarakhand</collectingRegion>
(formerly known as Uttaranchal). It was placed in 
<taxonomicName box="[1285,1376,255,279]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Flanona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1285,1376,255,279]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">Flanona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as it ‘resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Simon, 1898" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1898" box="[275,614,289,313]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Flanona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puellula">
<emphasis box="[275,462,289,313]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">Flanona puellula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Simon" box="[471,614,290,313]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" refString="Simon, E. (1898) Histoire naturelle des Araignees Seconde edition. Tome 2. Fascicule 2. Libraire encyclopedique de Roret, Paris, 188 pp. [pp. 193 - 380]" type="book chapter" year="1898">Simon, 1898</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
’ without providing any further detail. The original description provided no information on its genitalic morphology, other than the two illustrations of the 
<taxonomicName box="[1011,1118,325,348]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Epigynum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="149" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">epigynum</taxonomicName>
and internal female genitalia (
<bibRefCitation author="Biswas" box="[158,528,360,383]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" refString="Biswas, B. &amp; Roy, R. (2008) Description of six new species of spiders of the genera Lathys (Family: Dictynidae), Marpissa (Family: Salticidae), Misumenoides (Family: Thomisidae), Agroeca (Family: Clubionidae), Gnaphosa (Family: Gnaphosidae) and Flanona (Family: Lycosidae) from India. Records of the Zoological Survey of India, 108, 43 - 57." type="journal article" year="2008">Biswas &amp; Roy 2008: figs 17–18</bibRefCitation>
). The eye pattern illustrated for this species does not conform to the typical eye arrangement of lycosid spiders (4+2+2). Available illustrations suggest this species belong to the agelenid genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Ovtchinnikov, 1999" authorityName="Ovtchinnikov" authorityYear="1999" box="[151,511,429,452]" class="Arachnida" family="Amaurobiidae" genus="Draconarius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,287,429,452]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">Draconarius</emphasis>
Ovtchinnikov, 1999
</taxonomicName>
: shape of prosoma and opisthosoma, pattern of eye arrangement, larger posterior row of eyes, 
<taxonomicName box="[254,361,464,487]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Epigynum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="149" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">epigynum</taxonomicName>
with median atrium and large spermathecae encircled with copulatory ducts. Based on these resemblances, we propose to transfer 
<taxonomicName box="[552,691,497,521]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Flanona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="harduarae">
<emphasis box="[552,691,497,521]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">Z. harduarae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName box="[726,862,498,521]" class="Arachnida" family="Amaurobiidae" genus="Draconarius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[726,862,498,521]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">Draconarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
